   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>"I am Viktor the son of Matthew, the man of Sou (?) of the district of Eshmounain, writing to Apa Enoch, the monk of the (monastery ?) of Apa Apollo: I owe you thirty - that which is determined by (?) your measure. These then I am ready to . . . . . . to you in the yield of the twelfth year of the indiction, without any ambiguity. I, Viktor the son of Matthew, agree to this document. I, Pyew, the son of Papre, I do become his surety. I, Serenos the son of Viktor, and I Pakob the son of George, we are witnesses to this document. I, Paul the son of Joseph, I have written (it). Written in the month of Choiak, 15th (day), 12th year of the indiction.;(Verso): "Executed document of Viktor the son of Matthew (of the) village (of) Sou (?) . . . . . . . "</ab>
         </div>
